<div class="comment-wrapper"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/957b675456a66c394945a7361aedd51d?s=50"></div><header><strong>SourceKit limits on Swift refactoring</strong> from <string>Zhao Xin</string> &lt;owenzx at gmail.com&gt;<p>January 10, 2016 at 05:00:00am</p></header><div class="content"><p>There is a new Swift refactoring plugin<br>&lt;https://github.com/johnno1962/Refactorator&gt; for Xcode. It is developed<br>by johnno1962.<br></p><p>Tonight I have a conversation with him on an issue of the refactoring<br>plugin. The issue &lt;https://github.com/johnno1962/Refactorator/issues/3&gt; is<br>closed because johnno1962 says the issue is the limit of SourceKit, which<br>he can do nothing further.<br></p><p>So I bring it here and see if anyone can help.<br></p><p>The example is simple. Supposing we have code like this:<br></p><p>struct Person {<br>    var name:String<br></p><p>    init(aName:String) {<br>        self.name = aName<br>    }<br>}<br>func testOnly() {<br>    let john = Person(aName: &quot;John&quot;)<br></p><p>    print(john)<br>}<br></p><p><br>​When we do a refactor on aName, in ​let john = Person(aName: &quot;John&quot;).<br>SourceKit only find this line of code and the code line init(aName:String).<br></p><p>It should also find the code line: self.name = aName, which it didn&#39;t.<br></p><p>According to johnno1962, SourceKit treats the aName inside the<br>init(aName:String) as a variable different from the aName in<br>init(aName:String).<br></p><p>-- <br></p><p>​zhaoxin​<br>-------------- next part --------------<br>An HTML attachment was scrubbed...<br>URL: &lt;https://lists.swift.org/pipermail/swift-dev/attachments/20160110/8abe3db8/attachment.html&gt;<br></p></div><ul class="comments"><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3cc60df2d77f658efe8b66631a58b2fd?s=50"></div><header><strong>SourceKit limits on Swift refactoring</strong> from <string>Xi Ge</string> &lt;xi_ge at apple.com&gt;<p>January  9, 2016 at 01:00:00pm</p></header><div class="content"><p>Hi Xin,<br>I tried the case you gave here and got a SourceKit crash in the line of &quot;self.name = aName” when querying cursor info. I will get into this by Monday. <br>Thanks for letting us know!<br>Xi<br></p><p>&gt; On Jan 9, 2016, at 1:15 PM, 肇鑫 via swift-dev &lt;swift-dev at swift.org&gt; wrote:<br>&gt; <br>&gt; SourceKit<br></p><p>-------------- next part --------------<br>An HTML attachment was scrubbed...<br>URL: &lt;https://lists.swift.org/pipermail/swift-dev/attachments/20160109/b87ddefe/attachment.html&gt;<br></p></div><ul class="comments"><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/957b675456a66c394945a7361aedd51d?s=50"></div><header><strong>SourceKit limits on Swift refactoring</strong> from <string>Zhao Xin</string> &lt;owenzx at gmail.com&gt;<p>January 10, 2016 at 10:00:00am</p></header><div class="content"><p>Thanks. Refactor really makes working much easier. Looking forward to the<br>progress.<br></p><p>zhaoxin<br></p><p>On Sun, Jan 10, 2016 at 5:37 AM, Xi Ge &lt;xi_ge at apple.com&gt; wrote:<br></p><p>&gt; Hi Xin,<br>&gt; I tried the case you gave here and got a SourceKit crash in the line of &quot;<br>&gt; self.name = aName” when querying cursor info. I will get into this by<br>&gt; Monday.<br>&gt; Thanks for letting us know!<br>&gt; Xi<br>&gt;<br>&gt; On Jan 9, 2016, at 1:15 PM, 肇鑫 via swift-dev &lt;swift-dev at swift.org&gt; wrote:<br>&gt;<br>&gt; SourceKit<br>&gt;<br>&gt;<br>&gt;<br></p><p><br>-- <br></p><p>Owen Zhao<br>-------------- next part --------------<br>An HTML attachment was scrubbed...<br>URL: &lt;https://lists.swift.org/pipermail/swift-dev/attachments/20160110/11ad8067/attachment.html&gt;<br></p></div><ul class="comments"><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3cc60df2d77f658efe8b66631a58b2fd?s=50"></div><header><strong>SourceKit limi